Step 0
Namespace Quota

Step 1
apiVersion: v1
kind: ResourceQuota
metadata:
  name: pod-demo
spec:
  hard:
    pods: "1"

Step 2
kubectl get ns
kubectl describe ns 
kubectl create -f quota.txt
kubectl describe ns quota
kubectl run pods..

Step 3
kubectl edit ns quota
kubectl get pods -w
?Keep observing


Step 1:
Observe a Priority Class:
kubectl get pods -n kube-system
kubectl describe pod etcd-minikube -n kube-system
kubectl get priorityclass

Step 2:
=======
Define a Priority Class
notepad priority.txt
====================

apiVersion: scheduling.k8s.io/v1
kind: PriorityClass
metadata:
  name: high-priority
value: 1000000
globalDefault: false
description: "This priority class should be used for XYZ service pods only."

#preemptionPolicy: Never will be scheduled ahead of other jobs.

Step 3:
========
# kubectl create -f priority.txt
Now ,lets associate a priority class to quota.

apiVersion: v1
kind: List
items:
- apiVersion: v1
  kind: ResourceQuota
  metadata:
    name: pods-high
  spec:
    hard:
      cpu: "1000"
      memory: 200Gi
      pods: "10"
    scopeSelector:
      matchExpressions:
      - operator : In
        scopeName: PriorityClass
        values: ["high-priority"]
- apiVersion: v1
  kind: ResourceQuota
  metadata:
    name: pods-medium
  spec:
    hard:
      cpu: "10"
      memory: 20Gi
      pods: "10"
    scopeSelector:
      matchExpressions:
      - operator : In
        scopeName: PriorityClass
        values: ["medium"]
- apiVersion: v1
  kind: ResourceQuota
  metadata:
    name: pods-low
  spec:
    hard:
      cpu: "5"
      memory: 10Gi
      pods: "10"
    scopeSelector:
      matchExpressions:
      - operator : In
        scopeName: PriorityClass
        values: ["low"]


Step 4:
# kubectl create -f quotas.txt
# kubectl describe quota 
? observe the quotas arent utilized yet.

Step 5:
Now, Lets create a pod with Priority Class -- High-Priority

notepad podpri.txt
=================
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: high-priority
spec:
  containers:
  - name: high-priority
    image: ubuntu
    command: ["/bin/sh"]
    args: ["-c", "while true; do echo hello; sleep 10;done"]
    resources:
      requests:
        memory: "10Gi"
        cpu: "500m"
      limits:
        memory: "10Gi"
        cpu: "500m"
  priorityClassName: high-priority

#kubectl create -f podpri.txt
#kubectl get pods
#kubectl describe pod high-priority
#kubectl describe quota
? do you observe utilization
 
